<div class="adv-card"><div class="adv-icon">&#128274;</div><h3>Goods security</h3><p>24/7 security, CCTV, access control. Warehouse goods insurance. Temperature and humidity monitoring.</p></div>
<div class="adv-card"><div class="adv-icon">&#128640;</div><h3>Fast onboarding</h3><p>From the first call to the first shipment &mdash; 1-3 days. CRM integration in 2 hours. Seamless migration from your old warehouse.</p></div>
</div>
</div></section>

<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="faq"><div class="ctr">
<div class="badge">FAQ</div>
<h2 class="sec-h2">Frequently asked questions</h2>
<div class="faq-list">
<div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q">What is the minimum storage area?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>There is no minimum area &mdash; you only pay for the actual volume of goods in cubic metres. The minimum monthly fee is 5,000 UAH, which covers storage and basic services. This is more cost-effective than renting even the smallest warehouse.</p></div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q">Is there temperature control in the warehouse?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>Yes. Both warehouses are heated and humidity-controlled. The temperature is maintained between 15-25&deg;C year-round. This is suitable for most product categories: cosmetics, electronics, clothing, accessories, household chemicals.</p></div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q">How does the WMS system work?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>WMS (Warehouse Management System) is a warehouse management platform. Each product receives a barcode, each bin gets a unique address. Orders arrive automatically via API from your CRM, the system generates an optimal picking route, checks picking accuracy and prints shipping labels. You can see stock levels and order statuses in real time through your personal dashboard.</p></div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q">Can you store oversized goods?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>Yes. For oversized and heavy goods (50+ kg) we offer pallet storage from 450 UAH/pallet/mo. Racking supports loads up to 2 tonnes per tier. The warehouse has forklifts and hydraulic pallet jacks for moving pallets.</p></div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q">How quickly can we get started?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>Onboarding takes 1-3 days. Day 1: consultation and contract. Day 2: goods transfer to the warehouse, WMS scanning, CRM integration. Day 3: test shipments and launch. Most clients start shipping orders on day 2.</p></div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q">What happens during power outages?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>The Shchaslive warehouse is equipped with 3 generators and Starlink. Two fibre-optic ISPs provide backup internet. Since 2022, zero days of downtime. Orders are shipped on schedule regardless of the power situation.</p></div></div>
</div>
</div></section>

<!-- SEO ARTICLE -->
<section class="article-section">
<div class="ctr">
<div class="badge badge-dark">GOOD TO KNOW</div>
<h2>How to Choose a Warehouse for Your Online Store in Kyiv</h2>
<div class="article-content">
<h3>Why does an online store need an external warehouse?</h3>
<p>When an online store grows to 30-50 orders per day, maintaining your own warehouse becomes a separate challenge. Renting premises, warehouse staff salaries, utilities, packing materials &mdash; all of this adds up to 40,000-60,000 UAH per month even for a small warehouse. And that is without factoring in the owner's time, who ends up solving logistics problems instead of growing the business.</p>
<p>An external warehouse with fulfillment services means handing over all warehouse logistics to a professional operator. You store your goods at their warehouse, and they receive, store, pick and ship orders. For your customer, nothing changes &mdash; the parcel arrives as usual. For you, everything changes: instead of daily warehouse work &mdash; a dashboard review once a week.</p>

<h3>What to look for when choosing a warehouse</h3>
<p>First &mdash; location. A warehouse near Kyiv is the optimal choice for most online stores in Ukraine. From here, delivery via Nova Poshta to anywhere in the country is the fastest &mdash; the vast majority of parcels arrive within 1-2 days. MTP Group has two warehouses in the Kyiv region: in Shchaslive (Boryspil district, 2,800 m&sup2;) and Bilohorodka (1,100 m&sup2;).</p>
<p>Second &mdash; a warehouse management system (WMS). Without a WMS, a warehouse is just a room with shelves. With a WMS, every product has a barcode, every bin has an address, every order has a picking route. This delivers 99.7% accuracy and 30-second order assembly instead of 5-10 minutes by hand.</p>

<h3>How much does goods storage near Kyiv cost in 2026</h3>
<p>The cost of warehouse services depends on the volume of goods and the number of operations. Key components: storage &mdash; from 650 UAH per cubic metre per month, pallet storage &mdash; from 450 UAH per pallet per month, goods receiving &mdash; from 3 UAH per unit (up to 2 kg). The minimum monthly fee is 5,000 UAH.</p>
<p>For comparison: renting a 100 m&sup2; warehouse space near Kyiv costs 15,000-25,000 UAH/mo before utilities. Add a warehouse worker salary (18,000-25,000 UAH), packing materials, internet, security &mdash; and you are looking at 50,000+ UAH per month. A fulfillment warehouse for the same volumes starts at 10,000-20,000 UAH.</p>

<h3>Security and uninterrupted operations</h3>
<p>For an online store, it is critical that the warehouse operates without interruptions. Power cuts, internet issues, broken heating &mdash; any downtime means delayed orders and unhappy customers. That is why, when choosing a warehouse, you should ask about backup power.</p>
<p>The MTP Group warehouse in Shchaslive has three generators and Starlink. Two fibre-optic ISPs provide backup internet. Since 2022 &mdash; zero days of downtime due to blackouts. Both warehouses have 24/7 security, CCTV and access control. Temperature is maintained between 15-25&deg;C, which is suitable for the vast majority of product categories.</p>

<h3>How to connect to the MTP Group warehouse</h3>
<p>The onboarding process takes 1-3 days. Day one &mdash; consultation: we discuss volumes, product specifics, integration with your CRM. Day two &mdash; goods transfer to the warehouse, WMS scanning, test shipments. Day three &mdash; full launch. Integration with KeyCRM, SalesDrive, Horoshop, Shopify, WooCommerce, Prom.ua, Rozetka or any other platform with an API takes 2-4 hours.</p>
<p>Over 10 years of operation and 150+ onboarded online stores, we have refined this process to perfection. From the first call to the first shipment &mdash; 3 days maximum.</p>
</div>
</div>
</section>

